		"text_en": "Visual: The protagonist looks at One in disbelief. One's compromise instantly drains the last bit of courage to stick to logic. In Gloria's narrative, the protagonist has become the 'perpetrator' who destroys team harmony and hurts teammates' feelings.\nGloria (resuming her loving expression, gently grasping the protagonist's stiff hand): 'See, as long as we have the will to sacrifice and tolerate, the problem doesn't exist. Don't let your hatred and fear be so great. Try to forget the logic behind and work on the faith ahead. As long as you're a good person and believe in FSM, miracles will happen tomorrow.'\nGloria (with an almost commanding gentle tone): 'Now, say with me: Thank you FSM for the test, I am willing to let go of all anxiety.'\nVisual: The storm still rages outside, the purifier's red light still silently flashing. The protagonist looks at Gloria's expectant eyes, then at One who's willingly not fighting for anything.\nA deep sense of suffocation wells up. The protagonist realizes there might be a need to try.\nProtagonist (voice hoarse, submitting to this mental control, mechanically repeating): '...Thank you FSM for the test, I am willing to... let go of all anxiety.'\nVisual: Gloria smiles with satisfaction, the greenhouse once again filled with the false peace of 'toxic positivity.' But in the protagonist's heart, there's still a confused feeling.\nScreen slowly darkens, subtitles emerge: [The Next Day: The Miracle Didn't Come, But 'Heroes' Did.]\n[Pages 11-15 Complete, Fatal PUA Night Ends]",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_15_story_submit.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_16_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 16",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_16_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Scene: Next morning at the 'Greenhouse.'\nVisual: The water purifier has completely stopped working, emitting a burnt smell. The protagonist, lips cracked from dehydration, prepares to check the rusty 'Agency Dispatch Printer' (GDA's device for issuing scavenging permits) for water source commissions.\nSuddenly, the printer emits harsh gear-grinding sounds and spits out a red-stamped cowhide paper.\nThe protagonist tears off the paper, which reads: [Personnel Change Notice: Scavenger codenamed 'ARK' has been forcibly filled into your squad's vacancy through FSM's special approval loophole.]\nProtagonist (jumping up, gripping the paper tightly): 'Who the hell is this?! One, did you submit a recruitment application to the agency? Do you know him?'\nOne (looking bewildered, shaking his head, signing): '(No, I've never even heard this name.)'\nProtagonist (grinding teeth, slapping the paper on the table): 'A complete stranger, no greeting, just barging through backdoor channels into our team? Look at this attached personnel file, completely blank resume, not even a headshot, the only stamp date is this morning! This is definitely trouble!'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_16_story_ark_notice.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_17_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 17",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_17_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Visual: Gloria, having just finished her morning prayer in the corner, walks over with a saintly smile, gently picking up the cowhide paper.\nGloria (looking at the name, hands clasped at chest, eyes shining): 'Ark (Noah's Ark)... such a sacred name. You see, this is the 'Law of Attraction' at work! Just last night we entrusted our worries to FSM, and today He personally performs a miracle, arranging a new family member for us. This is the grace of the Flying Spaghetti Monster!'\nProtagonist (suppressing fury, trying to reason): 'Gloria, this isn't a miracle! We don't know him at all, don't know his background. In the wasteland, exposing your back to a stranger with no manners and unknown background equals suicide!'\nGloria (frowning slightly, tone carrying a hint of reproach): 'Why do you always think the worst of people? Maybe he's just a lonely soul looking for shelter. We should embrace him, give him love.'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_17_story_saint_smile.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_18_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 18",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_18_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Visual: Just then, the dispatch printer 'ka-chak ka-chak' sounds again. A remote telegraph from new member 'ARK' arrives.\nNo 'hello,' no 'please take care of me', the paper tape only prints a few cold commands.\nThe printer spits out: 'Team confirmed. Today's mission: Head to West District Scrapyard. I've already formulated a complete strategic schedule. Meet at scrapyard entrance at 12:00.'\n(Pause two seconds, machine spits another segment)\n'Wait, 12:00 might need to eat, change to 12:30.'\n(Pause three more seconds)\n'No, I still need to repair equipment. 13:00 meeting. Report immediately after reading.'\nProtagonist (laughing bitterly with anger, pointing at the pile of paper scraps): 'Is this guy sick?! He just joined, not even introducing himself, directly seizing the leader position and giving orders? And changed the meeting time three times, we haven't said a single word, and he's already made all the arrangements in a black box?!'\nGloria (gently patting the protagonist's arm, softly soothing): 'Relax. He's willing to proactively arrange the schedule, proving he's very responsible! We just need to obediently follow, wouldn't that be easier? Don't always feel others are targeting you, he just has more leadership talent.'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_18_story_ark_orders.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_19_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 19",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_19_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Visual: The protagonist is rendered speechless by Gloria's 'turning disasters into blessings' logic. One silently picks up a pen and signs the consent form, once again choosing compromise.\nThe protagonist is about to explode when suddenly a mechanical messenger pigeon, quite possibly guided by the non-existent Flying Spaghetti Monster, flies in from outside the door, heavily slamming a parchment letter onto the table.\nThe envelope reads: [Application to Join from 'Glory Knight Donkey']\nVisual: The protagonist tears open the letter and reads aloud:\n'To the members of GDA1: I am a hero cursed by fate. My previous teammates were all a bunch of selfish, incompetent wastes! I bore all the hard work, but they dragged down my great plan to save the princess with their stupidity! I'm fed up with those burdens. I saw your team has a vacancy, so I've decided to grant you the honor of fighting alongside me. Immediately approve my joining.'\nProtagonist (dumbfounded, throwing the letter on the table): 'What kind of weirdo is this?! The entire letter is trampling on former teammates, pushing off all responsibility! This kind of person who only shifts blame, with a head full of feudal fairy tales and delusions of grandeur, absolutely cannot let him in!'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_19_story_donkey_letter.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_20_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 20",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_20_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Gloria (holding the letter, eyes welling with sympathetic tears): 'Oh my, he's so pitiful. He must have suffered great grievances in his previous team to write such a defensive letter. He's just a wounded hero longing to be accepted. This is also FSM's test for us, we must heal him with love.'\nProtagonist (losing it, snatching back the application): 'Gloria! Wake up! Every line of this is shirking responsibility. This kind of person will sell us out first when something goes wrong! I'm going to tear up this application right now!'\nVisual: As the protagonist prepares to destroy the letter, the dispatch printer suddenly emits an extremely harsh long beep, spitting out one last paper with an official steel seal.\nThe paper reads: [GDA1 File Update: New member 'Donkey' has successfully joined the team. Approver: Squad Strategist ARK. Team assembly complete.]\nProtagonist (eyes wide with shock): 'Ark?! How dare he bypass us and directly submit approval to FSM?!'\nGloria (happily clapping hands, smile dazzlingly suffocating): 'Wonderful! Ark is so decisive. Now we have a responsible strategist and a wounded hero. See, as long as we have love in our hearts without prejudice, the universe will send us the best team! GDA1, officially setting out today!'\nVisual: The protagonist stands in place, looking at Ark's cold command notes, at Donkey's absurd responsibility-shifting letter, then at Gloria's face full of 'love and tolerance' and silently bowing One.\nThe protagonist knows this isn't some cosmic blessing. This is a ghost ship hijacked by so-called 'miracles' and 'positive energy,' sailing toward destruction.\n[Pages 16-20 Complete, Act II: Toxic Teammates Assemble Ends]",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_20_story_gda_formed.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_21_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 21",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_21_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Scene: West District Scrapyard entrance. Acid rain just stopped, ground full of mud. 13:00.\nVisual: Protagonist and One arrive on time. Not far away stands a man wrapped like an iron barrel with a thick square gas mask, this is ARK. He holds a stack of densely gridded paper schedules.\nARK (voice muffled through mask, stiff and monotone): 'GDA1 squad. I am the strategic officer Ark for this operation. This is my 'Absolute Order Route Map' planned for the scrapyard. Do you have any opinions? We are a democratic team, welcome to propose.'\nProtagonist (taking the schedule, frowning): 'This route has problems. You're directing us toward the 'High Radiation Swamp Zone.' I checked the scrapyard terrain last night, taking the abandoned elevated bridge on the east is safe. This route is suicide.'\nARK (pushing his gas mask, checking a box on the schedule): 'Mm, I heard your opinion. However, I already submitted this route map as the final resolution to the agency system and locked it ten minutes ago. So we'll still follow my route. Let's go.'\nProtagonist (stunned): 'Then why the hell did you just ask for my opinion?! You call this democracy? This is a complete black box operation!'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_21_story_ark_arrives.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_22_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 22",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_22_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Visual: As the protagonist prepares to blow up, a man wearing flashy, shiny armor (actually made from hammered waste aluminum cans) with a tattered red cloth swaggers over. This is 'Glory Knight Donkey.'\nDonkey (striking an exaggerated heroic sword-drawing pose, loudly proclaiming): 'The gears of fate begin to turn! The dragon's roar echoes in the abyss! Everyone, Glory Knight Donkey makes his dazzling entrance! In this scrapyard, there must be a pure princess imprisoned waiting for me to rescue!'\nProtagonist (painfully clutching forehead): 'This is a scrapyard! Only rusty metal sheets and mutated rats! Where are these princesses and dragons you're talking about? Is there something wrong with your brain?'\nGloria (walking up with a bright smile, hands clasped looking at Donkey): 'Oh my, Donkey, your energy frequency is so high! Look at the light shining in his eyes, this is the heroic spirit our team needs. We can't use worldly perspectives to limit his imagination.'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_22_story_donkey_entrance.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_23_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 23",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_23_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Visual: The protagonist takes a deep breath, deciding to give up arguing common sense with them, turning instead to handle the immediate survival problem.\nProtagonist (calming down): 'Whatever. But entering the radiation zone requires a 'detector.' Our team's quota is long used up. Without a detector, going in is suicide.'\nGloria (suddenly pulling out a rusty tin can from her white cloak, smiling sweetly): 'Don't worry, leave it to me! Yesterday I met a wandering merchant and traded half our team's rations for this 'Soul Detector'!'\nVisual: The protagonist takes the tin can. It's not a detector at all, just a broken can with a crooked sunflower painted in cheap watercolor, and English chicken soup written on the bottom: 'Be your own sunshine.'\nProtagonist (hands trembling with anger): 'Gloria! You've been scammed! This is just broken garbage! The pointer inside is painted on! You traded half our survival rations for trash?!'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_23_story_fake_detector.png",
