	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_24_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 24",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_24_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Gloria (smile not diminishing, looking at protagonist with compassionate eyes): 'Scammed? Why use such a negative word? Though it doesn't have what the worldly define as 'function,' it's an environmentally-friendly art piece full of stories! When you feel fear in the scrapyard, looking at this sunflower, you can find inner light.'\nGloria (approaching protagonist, tone gentle yet carrying strong manipulation): 'You're too obsessed with 'useful' and 'useless.' Your anger is actually a projection of your inner lack of security. As long as we have light in our hearts and don't admit this is a scam, it's a gift from FSM. You must learn gratitude.'\nVisual: The protagonist is shocked speechless by this 'forcibly turning bad into good' logic. Knowing reasoning with these people is useless, they can only rely on themselves.\nProtagonist (grinding teeth, pulling from backpack a hand-drawn detailed map and safety guidelines worked on all last night): 'Enough. I don't want to hear your spiritual chicken soup. I stayed up all night comparing three years of scavenging data and drew this 'Safety Avoidance Map,' marking all hidden toxic pits. Each of you take one, follow the markers and we can survive.'",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_24_story_safety_map.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_25_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 25",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_25_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Visual: The protagonist hands over the life-saving map condensing so much effort to teammates. This is the greatest effort made for team survival.\nDonkey (casually taking the map, not even looking, directly folding it into a paper airplane and forcefully throwing it into the air): 'I don't see any map. Are there even maps? Seems like no one has gone in before, so there aren't any. Why don't we just go in directly!'\nARK (not even extending a hand, coldly saying through the mask): 'I also don't see any map. You didn't see it either, right? There probably was never anyone who went in before, so there isn't one.'\nGloria (not seeing the map): 'Never mind, then let's just go in directly ourselves. As long as we set out with love and tolerance, we have nothing to fear. Let's go!'\nVisual: The protagonist freezes in place. The life-saving map worked on all night is trampled in the mud, no one looks at it, no one even knows, no one cares. One hasn't had time to respond before being pulled away by Gloria with a smile.\nThe protagonist watches these teammates cheerfully walking toward the death swamp. Deep inside, a chill called 'exhaustion and despair' completely consumes them.\n[Pages 21-25 Complete, Act III: Casting Pearls Before Swine Ends]",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_25_story_map_ignored.png",
	},
	{
