		"title_en": "Page 26",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_26_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Scene: Inside West District Scrapyard, Contamination Sorting Area.\nVisual: Surroundings piled with faintly glowing radioactive waste. The squad faces their first cooperation task: clearing a safe passage to the core area.\nThe protagonist prepares to spread out the hand-drawn map to assign positions, but ARK suddenly pulls out three sets of old tactical radio microphones just found from his backpack. Without hesitation, he hands two sets to Gloria and Donkey, putting on the last set himself. The three immediately form a tight small circle, backs turned to the protagonist and One.\nProtagonist: 'Ark, what are you doing? We have five people here. You only take three microphones for connection, why separate us?'\nARK (turning head, tone full of blind confidence and dismissiveness): 'No worries. Equipment is limited. I already have the perfect plan in mind, leave it to me. You don't need to worry about details.'",
