		"title_en": "Page 29",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_29_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Gloria (hurrying over, shielding ARK, addressing protagonist in gentle yet barbed tone): 'Oh dear, why are you angry again? No worries, the three of us just had a very smooth discussion. We can 'translate' the conclusion to One later, can't we? Why must you force everyone to cater to your so-called 'fairness'?'\nGloria (turning to One, revealing a patronizing smile): 'One, you don't mind, right? We're all working for the team.'\nOne (body stiffening slightly. To avoid breaking this 'harmony,' he forces a smile uglier than crying): '...I don't mind. I'll just follow arrangements.'\nVisual: The protagonist looks at One's accommodating appearance, feeling as if their heart was viciously stabbed. They see their past self, isolated in the camp, silently enduring.",
