		"title_en": "Page 31",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_31_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Protagonist (pointing at the completely silent southeast, unable to take it anymore): 'Bullshit! There's not even a ghost there! You're just trying to escape this dirty, exhausting work!'\nDonkey (violently throwing off tattered red cloth cape, righteously shouting): 'How can vulgar mortals understand a hero's mission?! Moving a broken iron door, how can that compare with the great glory of rescuing a princess?! Fate is calling me, I must go ahead first!'\nVisual: After speaking, Donkey actually turns and runs, disappearing around a scrapyard corner like the wind.\nThe protagonist freezes in place, looking at ARK: 'This is your 'No worries' plan?!'\nARK (shrugging, still relaxed): 'No worries, it's just a door. Someone will move it eventually. Relax.'",
