		"title_en": "Page 34",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_34_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Visual: The air instantly drops to freezing. ARK frowns, seeming to feel the protagonist has disrupted his 'No worries' atmosphere.\nAnd Gloria slowly opens her eyes. She doesn't look at injured One, doesn't look at the iron frame that nearly killed someone. She looks at the protagonist, no longer with gentleness, but with a superior, bone-chillingly disappointing gaze.\nAt this moment, Gloria's broken radio in her pocket, due to poor contact, automatically starts playing Teacher Chan's song, the gentle melody echoing in the dangerous scrapyard:\n'[Singing] Let me be my own protagonist... Success or failure depends on how I see it...'\nGloria (accompanied by Teacher Chan's singing, voice incredibly gentle yet wrapping around the protagonist's neck like a poisonous snake): 'Do you know how hurtful your words just were? I've always been tolerating you, even tolerating and accepting your usual double-speed, oppressively pressured way of speaking. But I've discovered I was wrong.'",
