		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_35_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 35",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_35_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Gloria (stepping forward, eyes filled with moral judgment's oppressive weight, launching merciless manipulation): 'Have you forgotten love and tolerance? Donkey is just pursuing his dream. Ark just doesn't want to pressure everyone. But you? Your powerful negative energy is destroying our entire energy field! You always use your cold logic to nitpick others. You think you're solving problems? No, you're creating division!'\nGloria (eyes welling with tears, as if she's the biggest victim): 'I just came to this wasteland, living in fear every day. It's your negative energy that slowly led me into my first emotional low point in life! Actually, most times, as long as you treat others with kindness, don't stab people in the back, don't have such a heavy hatred heart, people wouldn't dislike you at all! Why can't you be more generous and entrust everything to the Flying Spaghetti Monster, to FSM?! Everyone can shine, you just haven't found the right place yet, though the right place might be where you are after you're dead.'\nVisual: The protagonist gasps heavily, lips trembling as they prepare to retort. Against Teacher Chan's 'Everyone can shine' background music, Gloria's words hammer down like a heavy weight, shattering the protagonist's last inner defenses.\nLooking at tears in Gloria's eyes, the long-standing desire for 'kindred spirits' and fear of loneliness completely backlashes at this moment.",
		"image_path": "res://1.Codebase/src/assets/ui/intro/page_35_story_protagonist_breakdown.png",
	},
	{
		"title_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_36_TITLE",
		"title_en": "Page 36",
		"text_zh": "INTRO_DATA_PAGE_36_TEXT",
		"text_en": "Protagonist (pupils violently shaking, inner rationality completely collapsing): [She's crying... Did I drag her into an emotional low? Is my logic too cold? Do I speak too fast, too aggressively? So the problem has always been with me... My pathetic past turned me into this negative energy monster...]\nVisual: The protagonist looks at their own fists clenched in anger, suddenly feeling intense self-loathing. They slowly release their hands, legs weakening, actually half-kneeling in the muddy water.\nProtagonist (voice hoarse, filled with remorse and deep guilt): 'I'm sorry... Gloria. You're right. It's my fault. I'm too sensitive, my hatred heart too heavy. I... I've been living in past shadows, venting these negative energies on you all. Sorry, I'm truly sorry.'\nGloria (the coldness in her eyes instantly dissipates, replaced by an extremely loving, saintly smile. She extends her hand, gently stroking the protagonist's head): 'It's okay. As long as you're willing to admit your weakness, FSM will forgive you. Come, let's entrust these troubles we can't handle together to Him.'\n[Act IV: The Nominal Assembly and True Test]",
